rComments: I took Dr. Eastwood's Contemporary American Fiction class and loved it. His lecture style is engaging and he did a great job of fostering discussion and keeping it on point. The syllabus was excellent and I developed a huge appreciation for this area thanks to the course. He is also very approachable and helpful when it comes to assignments

Eastwood lacks structure with his lectures and leaves most of the work to the students' (sometimes very off topic) discussion. He makes irrelevant pop-culture references, has a rambling, pretentious sounding lecture style, and is not very helpful at answering questions. Avoid
